    "q7":"By enforcing the City Charter, the Maryland Declaration of Rights, and Article XI of the Maryland Constitution, as it relates to Baltimore City</p>",
    "q8":"The City Council has since 1967 has helped to sell off all of the City's assets from its interest in BGE, Friendship Airport, Ft. Smallwood Park, Baltimore City Hospital, The Baltimore Zoo, The Baltimore Jail, the Baltimore Aquarium, the Baltimore Science Center and others.</p><p>They have closed schools, rec centers, have allowed more than 100 million dollars to go missing from the Baltimore City Public Schools and no one has been held accountable.</p><p>There hasn't been an real audit in more than 30 years.</p><p>Police Brutality, lead in the schools water supply and public housing, the towing scandal, the police evidence locker scandal I could go on and on with what has been allowed to happen by people who have spent 10, 20 and some even 35+ years in office.</p>",
    "q9":"For every contract to be valid, there must be an offer, a consideration, and an agreement----The City doesn't offer services, unless you live in Roland Park, Guilford, Homeland, Homewood or some other affluent white area, but if you're working class, and or poor the City issues dictates.</p><p>When the women of Gilmore Homes were being raped, what service did Paul Grazziano offer to them?</p><p>When the people were complaining about police brutality and murder under color of law, what services did the city offer them?</p><p>What can be done to improve City services, removing every incumbent and their patronage cronies from office is the only thing that will improve city services.</p>",
